* Program: Inline Comment Handling
* Description: Natural comment forms - full-line (* / **) and rest-of-line (/*)
** A double-asterisk line is also a full-line comment.
*
DEFINE DATA LOCAL
1 #MSG1 (A50)
1 #MSG2 (A50)
1 #A (I4)
1 #B (I4)
1 #C (I4)
END-DEFINE
*
* CALLNAT with a rest-of-line comment after the statement
CALLNAT 'MYPROG' /* call to myprog
*
* Rest-of-line comment after an assignment
MOVE 'hello' TO #MSG1 /* first assignment
MOVE 'world' TO #MSG2 /* second assignment
*
* A mid-line asterisk is multiplication, NOT a comment
COMPUTE #A = #B * #C /* product, then comment to end of line
*
* No nesting and no closer: everything after /* is comment,
* including any later */ which is just comment text, not code
MOVE 1 TO #A /* comment with /* inside */ still all comment
*
END
